---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Track Easy - Support"
  description="Get help with Track Easy - Simple Habit Tracker iOS app."
  ogUrl="https://idlefusion.com/track-easy/support"
>
  <main>
    <section class="section-padding">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-8">Support</h1>

        <div class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-12">
          <p class="text-lg mb-4">Need help with Track Easy?</p>
          <p>Send us an email at <a href="mailto:support@idlefusion.com?subject=Track%20Easy%20Support%20Request" class="text-[var(--accent-primary)] hover:underline">support@idlefusion.com</a> and we'll get back to you as soon as we can.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="space-y-8 text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">How do I create a habit?</h3>
            <p>Tap the + button on the main screen. Enter a name, pick an icon and color, choose your schedule, and tap Save. Your habit is ready to track.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">How do streaks work?</h3>
            <p>A streak counts consecutive completions based on your habit's schedule. If your habit is set for weekdays only, weekends don't break your streak. Your current streak and personal best are shown on the habit card.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">Can I track a habit multiple times per day?</h3>
            <p>Yes! When creating or editing a habit, you can set a daily target greater than one. Tap the habit multiple times to log each completion.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">What schedule options are available?</h3>
            <p>Track Easy supports daily habits, weekday-only, weekend-only, specific days of the week, or a flexible "X times per week" goal. Choose whatever fits your routine.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">How do I add widgets to my home screen?</h3>
            <p>Long-press on your home screen, tap the + button in the top corner, search for "Track Easy," and choose a widget size. You can check off habits directly from the widget.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">Does Track Easy work on Apple Watch?</h3>
            <p>Yes. The Apple Watch app shows today's habits and lets you mark them complete with a tap. It syncs automatically with your iPhone.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">Where is my data stored?</h3>
            <p>All data is stored locally on your device. Nothing is sent to the cloud or any server. Your habits are completely private.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">How do I transfer my data to a new device?</h3>
            <p>Track Easy data is included in your standard iCloud or iTunes backup. Restore your backup on your new device and your habits will be there.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">Can I edit or delete past completions?</h3>
            <p>Yes. Open the Calendar view, tap on any day, and you can toggle completions on or off for that date.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
